data.title: Coblenz
meta_keywords: Meyers Gazetteer of the German Empire
data.meta_description: The historical entry for Coblenz, Coblenz, including parish and jurisdiction information, in the Meyers Gazetteer of the German Empire also known as Meyers Orts- und Verkehrs-Lexikon des Deutschen Reichs.
data.text:
Type HptSt. d. pr. Rheinprov. u. d. RB. Coblenz; StKr. - Coblenz is a HptSt. d. pr. Rheinprov. u. d. RB. Coblenz; StKr.

OLG Cöln - The Oberlandesgericht for Coblenz is in Cöln. The Oberlandesgericht is where the Higher Court is located.

AG Coblenz [self] - The Amtsgericht for Coblenz is in itself. The Amtsgericht is where the Lower District Court is located.

LG Coblenz [self] - The Landgericht for Coblenz is in itself. The Landgericht is where the District Court is located.

BKdo Coblenz [self] - The Bezirkskommando for Coblenz is in itself. The Bezirkskommando is the District Military Command. You can look in the BKdo to find military records.

StdA Coblenz [self] - The Standesamt for Coblenz is in itself. The Standesamt is where the Civil Registration Office is located.

kath. Pfk. 9 - Coblenz has 9 katholisch Pfarrkirche (Catholic parish churches).

ev. K. 3 - Coblenz has 3 evangelisch Kirche (Protestant Churches).

Syn 1 - Coblenz has 1 Synagoge (Synagogue).

Other 1 - Coblenz has 1 church that is not an evangelical church, Catholic church, or Synagogue.
